    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Substantive due process is a crucial aspect of the 14th Amendment that has been instrumental in protecting civil rights and personal liberties. By striking down laws that infringe upon fundamental rights, such as reproductive freedom (Roe v. Wade) and LGBTQ+ rights (Lawrence v. Texas), the Supreme Court has consistently demonstrated its commitment to safeguarding individual autonomy and dignity. This doctrine has also been used to limit government overreach, as seen in cases like Griswold v. Connecticut, which protected marital privacy, and Obergefell v. Hodges, which guaranteed same-sex marriage.",
