      "content": "I see. So you're saying procedural due process is basically just a limited version of what we really need? If I'm teaching this, I don't want to make it sound like the \"procedural\" side is just an incomplete or lesser way of looking at things. Do you think there's a valid legal argument that substantive due process is actually unconstitutional because it gives too much power to judges?",
